1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a method for enabling dense SDM (Supervised Descent Method) on a mobile device, which is a common problem in computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a Sparse Compositional Regression (SCR) framework, which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with feature extraction and processing, which is a common problem in multimedia applications. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper proposes a binary approximation to SIFT features, which is a commonly used feature in AI applications. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with real-time processing of dense features on a mobile device, which is a common problem in graphics applications.
